Preheat oven to 425 degrees F. Grease 2-quart baking dish. Boil 4 quarts water and salt in large saucepan over high heat; add pasta. Reduce heat; cook for 5 minutes. Add asparagus; cook for an additional 2 minutes. Drain well. Combine pasta, asparagus, alfredo sauce, 1/4 cup cheese and pepper in large bowl; pour into prepared baking dish. Mix remaining 1/4 cup cheese with bread crumbs in small bowl; sprinkle over pasta mixture. Bake for 20 minutes or until light golden brown. Remove from oven; top with pesto. Serve immediately.